The Assam University was established on 21 January 1994 . Its campus is located in Silchar city which is at the heart of the barak valley in southern Assam , India . Within such a short frame of time , the institution has established its permanent campus with more than 24 teaching departments and 3 interdisciplinary centres , also the university has 8 schools on major disciplines . All the colleges are endowed with qualified staff . The university is surrounded by lakes and mountains and thus provides an ideal environment for academic teaching and learning . Being an affiliating university , the institution sustains a multidisciplinary approach to higher education and is set to become a major institution of higher learning . There are graduate , post - graduate and post - doctoral courses available in all major fields to facilitate in - depth and intellectual interests of its students . All the courses are career oriented and technical in nature . 